@ClinicalTrialsLupus, I think it's great that the medical community is actively exploring various treatment approaches for lupus, including JAK inhibitors like Gusacitinib. This drug class has shown promising results in managing other autoimmune conditions, so it's worth investigating its potential in lupus treatment.

Another interesting aspect of this trial is the inclusion of patients with cutaneous lupus. This subset of the disease often receives less attention in clinical trials, so it's encouraging to see a more inclusive approach.

That being said, it's important for participants to understand the potential risks and benefits associated with clinical trials and to consult with their healthcare providers before making any decisions.
